"title": "8800: prejudice",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8800: prejudice",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Seen mainly in Scripture as a bias against places, peoples and ideas. It is sometimes so firmly rooted as to resist all contrary evidence.</p>\n<h2>Prejudice against places</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:46\">JHN 1:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:41\">JHN 7:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:52\">JHN 7:52</a></p>\n<h2>Prejudice against people</h2>\n<h3>Prejudice due to an attitude of superiority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:49\">JHN 7:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:27\">1SA 10:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:10-1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:10–25:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:1-Job30:10\">JOB 30:1–30:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:5\">ISA 65:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:11\">LUK 18:11</a></p>\n<h3>Prejudice based on fear or jealousy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:9-Exod1:10\">EXO 1:9–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:12-Exod1:13\">EXO 1:12–1:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:8-1Sam18:9\">1SA 18:8–18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:29\">1SA 18:29</a></p>\n<h3>Prejudice against Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:37\">JHN 12:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:34\">MAT 9:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:2-Mark6:3\">MRK 6:2–6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:29\">JHN 9:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:20\">JHN 10:20</a></p>\n<h2>Prejudice may be based on false assumptions about people's behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Hostility incorrectly assumed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:11-Gen12:12\">GEN 12:11–12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:2\">GEN 20:1–20:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:1-Gen26:11\">GEN 26:1–26:11</a></p>\n<h3>Motives misunderstood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:5-Num32:9\">NUM 32:5–32:9</a></strong> <em>The leaders of Reuben and Gad chose to inhabit the fertile land in Transjordan but they were also prepared to cross the Jordan to help their brothers conquer the land.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:14\">NUM 32:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:17\">NUM 32:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:10-Josh22:24\">JOS 22:10–22:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:3\">2SA 10:3</a></p>\n<h2>Prejudice in terms of partiality</h2>\n<h3>Favouritism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:28\">GEN 25:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3\">GEN 37:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:20\">GEN 44:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:27-Gen44:29\">GEN 44:27–44:29</a></p>\n<h3>People are often prejudiced in favour of their own kind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:46-Matt5:47\">MAT 5:46–5:47</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:32-Luke6:34\">LUK 6:32–6:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:29\">LUK 7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:16\">LUK 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:45\">ACT 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:18\">LUK 11:18</a></p>\n<h3>Prejudice on grounds of outward appearance or behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:3-Jas2:4\">JAS 2:3–2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:25\">2SA 14:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:16\">ECC 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:15\">JHN 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1\">ROM 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:3\">ROM 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:10\">ROM 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:13\">ROM 14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:6\">GAL 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Prejudice due to race</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:5-Esth3:6\">EST 3:5–3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:15-Ezra4:16\">EZR 4:15–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:1-Neh4:4\">NEH 4:1–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:8-Esth3:14\">EST 3:8–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:4\">EST 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:8-Dan3:12\">DAN 3:8–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:3-Dan6:9\">DAN 6:3–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:13\">DAN 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Partiality forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:3\">EXO 23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15\">LEV 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:9\">JAS 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>God is not prejudiced</h2>\n<h3>God is impartial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:34\">ACT 10:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:11\">ROM 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:9\">EPH 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:25\">COL 3:25</a></p>\n<h3>Job falsely accuses God of partiality</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:16\">JOB 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:20\">JOB 9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:30-Job9:31\">JOB 9:30–9:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:15-Job10:17\">JOB 10:15–10:17</a></p>\n<h2>Prejudice which no contrary evidence would change</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:31\">LUK 16:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:13-1Sam22:15\">1SA 22:13–22:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:21-Matt11:23\">MAT 11:21–11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:32\">MAT 21:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52\">ACT 7:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:41\">ACT 13:41</a></p>\n<h2>The Sadducees' prejudice against the resurrection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:23\">MAT 22:23</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:18\">MRK 12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:27\">LUK 20:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:1-Acts4:3\">ACT 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:8\">ACT 23:8</a></p>",
